From: Paul Young <yyang173@illinois.edu>
Date: Wed, 20 Dec 2017 14:42:15 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] increase g(r) cutoff to Wigner-Seitz cell radius

g(r) max distance used to default to simulation cell radius. The past
default is not optimal for non-cubic cell where Wigner-Seitz cell radius
> simulation cell radius.
---
 src/QMCHamiltonians/PairCorrEstimator.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/QMCHamiltonians/PairCorrEstimator.cpp b/src/QMCHamiltonians/PairCorrEstimator.cpp
index eb4eac7094..ace9212ed6 100644
--- a/src/QMCHamiltonians/PairCorrEstimator.cpp
+++ b/src/QMCHamiltonians/PairCorrEstimator.cpp
@@ -35,7 +35,7 @@ PairCorrEstimator::PairCorrEstimator(ParticleSet& elns, std::string& sources)
   //use the simulation cell radius if any direction is periodic
   if(elns.Lattice.SuperCellEnum)
   {
-    Dmax=elns.Lattice.SimulationCellRadius;
+    Dmax=elns.Lattice.WignerSeitzRadius;
     Volume=elns.Lattice.Volume;
   }
   else
